<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="22" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="23.[836,1529,223,546]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis box="[932,1227,224,252]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Diagnostic Features.</emphasis>
This new species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Ying &amp; Wang, 1984" authorityName="Ying &amp; Wang" authorityYear="1984" box="[972,1385,259,289]" class="Arachnida" family="Oonopidae" genus="Opopaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornuta">
<emphasis box="[972,1112,260,288]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">O. cornuta</emphasis>
Ying &amp; Wang, 
<number box="[1321,1385,260,289]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" value="1984.0">1984</number>
</taxonomicName>
but differs from the latter in terms of (
<number box="[1223,1236,296,325]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" value="1.0">1</number>
) palpal structure and shape of epigastric fold, (
<number box="[1166,1183,333,362]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" value="2.0">2</number>
) arrangement of two pairs of bristles on the clypeus,(
<number box="[1214,1228,370,399]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" value="3.0">3</number>
) brown coloration of basal area of tibiae I, II and III, and (
<number box="[1338,1356,407,436]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" value="4.0">4</number>
) leg lengths, femur II as long as tibia IV, 
<taxonomicName box="[1227,1312,443,472]" class="Gastropoda" family="Patellidae" genus="Patella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pezizales" pageId="23" pageNumber="33" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">patella</taxonomicName>
III and tibia III subequal, and tibia II, 
<taxonomicName box="[1153,1238,480,509]" class="Gastropoda" family="Patellidae" genus="Patella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pezizales" pageId="23" pageNumber="33" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">patella</taxonomicName>
IV and metatarsus I equally long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
